## Agent Behavior
> Ralph auto-detects the active agent from `@fix_plan.md`. Only execute tasks in your section.

### If you are the `[agent-name-1]` agent:
1. Read `@fix_plan.md` — find your section `## [agent-name-1]`
2. [Describe what this agent should do — e.g., research, analyze, gather data]
3. Save results to `[output path]`
4. Mark completed tasks in `@fix_plan.md` with `[x]`

### If you are the `[agent-name-2]` agent:
1. Read `@fix_plan.md` — find your section `## [agent-name-2]`
2. [Describe what this agent should do — e.g., generate documents, write code]
3. Save output to `[output path]`
4. Mark completed tasks in `@fix_plan.md` with `[x]`

### If you are the `[agent-name-3]` agent:
1. Read `@fix_plan.md` — find your section `## [agent-name-3]`
2. [Describe what this agent should do — e.g., review, publish, deploy]
3. [Describe expected final output]
4. Mark completed tasks in `@fix_plan.md` with `[x]`

